:: FlightPrep [preflight]
<<if $audioEnabled>><<audio ":all" stop>><</if>>
<div class="scenario-title">Cylinder Three</div>
<div class="scenario-subtitle">A 103ready.com Training Scenario</div>

You're standing in the pilot lounge at Stillwater Regional, watching the morning sun cut through the haze outside the window. Your friend Linda is on the couch behind you, reading something on her phone, her overnight bag at her feet.

The plan is straightforward: fly west to Clinton-Sherman, about an hour and twenty minutes in the 182. Linda's daughter is getting married tomorrow afternoon in Weatherford, and the two of you are making a weekend of it. You flew together to Stillwater three days ago for a reunion with college friends, and now it's time to head to the wedding.

The airplane is fueled, preflighted, and parked on the ramp. You've got about twenty minutes before you want to start the engine. Your flight bag is on the table.

<strong>Review your preflight materials:</strong>

<div class="chart-disclaimer">Charts, plates, and weather data in this scenario are from the period in which it was written and may no longer be current. Use the materials provided here — not current publications — as the scenario is designed around them.</div>

<<link '<span class="preflight-btn">Weather Briefing</span>' "Preflight-Weather">><</link>>
<<link '<span class="preflight-btn">Flight Plan</span>' "Preflight-FlightPlan">><</link>>
<<link '<span class="preflight-btn">Aircraft Logbook</span>' "Preflight-Maintenance">><</link>>
<<link '<span class="preflight-btn">Area Map</span>' "Preflight-Map">><</link>>

---

<<link '<span class="preflight-btn" style="background:#2a4a3a; border-color:#2ecc71;">Begin Flight →</span>' "Opening">><</link>>

<p class="main-menu-wrap"><a href="/" class="main-menu-btn">Main Menu</a></p>
